2042875625193119, -0.05609762668609619, -0.05768276005983353, 0.008136648684740067, -0.0007529098656959832, 0.04513447731733322, 0.016882820054888725, -0.008229472674429417, 0.03162289783358574, 0.025237513706088066, 0.021557467058300972, 0.06677087396383286, 0.021660776808857918, 0.07797642797231674, 0.0012385620502755046, 0.05651947110891342, 0.013967915438115597, 0.013569163158535957, -0.04413532093167305, 0.01962340995669365, 0.09700510650873184, 0.0031323053408414125, 0.015791142359375954, -0.12587285041809082, -0.009595760144293308, -0.07020169496536255, -0.07586278021335602], "result": {"documents": ["Jazz is a music genre that originated in New Orleans in the early 20th century, blending African-American musical traditions with European harmonic structures. It is characterized by improvisation, brass instruments, syncopation, and swing rhythm.", "Blues is a music genre and musical form that originated in the Deep South of the United States around the 1860s. It uses call-and-response patterns, blue notes, and the twelve-bar harmonic structure, influencing nearly all modern American music.", "Funk is a music genre that originated in African-American communities in the mid-1960s, emphasizing groove, syncopated basslines, and rhythmic drumming. James Brown, Parliament-Funkadelic, and Earth, Wind & Fire are foundational artists.", "R&B, or rhythm and blues, is a genre of popular music that originated in African-American communities in the 1940s. It blends soulful vocals with funk and pop influences, with modern artists like Beyonc\u00c3\u00a9, Usher, and Alicia Keys.", "Soul music is a genre that originated in African-American communities in the United States during the 1950s and 1960s. It combines gospel vocal style with rhythm and blues, with legends like Aretha Franklin, Ray Charles, and Marvin Gaye."], "scores": [0.8397325420809498, 0.676898700117851, 0.6564009833024368, 0.6406902333415347, 0.6356361513763028], "model_name": "bge-small", "document_ids": ["Jazz", "Blues", "Funk", "R&B", "Soul"]}}